==Events== *[[1229]] &ndash; The [[Sixth Crusade]]: [[Frederick II, Holy Roman Emperor]] signs a ten-year [[truce]] with [[al-Kamil]], regaining [[Jerusalem]], [[Nazareth]], and [[Bethlehem]] with neither military engagements nor support from the [[papacy]]. *[[1268]] &ndash; The [[Livonian Order]] is defeated by [[Daumantas of Pskov|Dovmont]] of [[Pskov]] in the [[Battle of Wesenberg (1268)|Battle of Rakvere]]. *[[1332]] &ndash; [[Amda Seyon I]], [[Emperor of Ethiopia]] begins his campaigns in the southern [[Muslim]] provinces. *[[1478]] &ndash; [[George Plantagenet, 1st Duke of Clarence|George, Duke of Clarence]], convicted of [[treason]] against his older brother [[Edward IV of England]], is [[execution (legal)|executed]] in private at the [[Tower of London]]. *[[1637]] &ndash; [[Eighty Years' War]]: Off the coast of [[Cornwall]], England, a [[Spanish Empire|Spanish]] fleet [[Battle off Lizard Point|intercepts]] an important [[Kingdom of England|Anglo]]-[[Dutch Republic|Dutch]] merchant convoy of 44 vessels escorted by six warships, destroying or capturing 20 of them. *[[1745]] &ndash; The city of [[Surakarta]], [[Central Java]] is founded on the banks of [[Solo River|Bengawan Solo River]], and becomes the capital of the [[Sunanate of Surakarta|Sunanate of Surakarta Hadiningrat]]. *[[1766]] &ndash; A mutiny by captive [[Malagasy people|Malagasy]] begins at sea on the slave ship ''[[Meermin slave mutiny|''Meermin'']]'', leading to the ship's destruction on [[Cape Agulhas]] in present-day South Africa and the recapture of the instigators. *[[1781]] &ndash; [[Fourth Anglo-Dutch War]]: Captain Thomas Shirley [[Shirley's Gold Coast expedition|opens his expedition]] against [[Dutch Gold Coast|Dutch colonial outposts]] on the [[Gold Coast (British colony)|Gold Coast]] of Africa (present-day [[Ghana]]). *[[1791]] &ndash; Congress passes a law [[admission to the Union|admitting]] the state of [[Vermont]] to the Union, effective 4 March, after that state had existed for 14 years as a de facto independent largely unrecognized state. *[[1797]] &ndash; [[French Revolutionary Wars]]: Sir [[Ralph Abercromby]] and a fleet of 18 [[Kingdom of Great Britain|British]] warships [[Invasion of Trinidad (1797)|invade]] [[Trinidad]]. *[[1814]] &ndash; [[Napoleonic Wars]]: The [[Battle of Montereau]]. *[[1861]] &ndash; In [[Montgomery, Alabama]], [[Jefferson Davis]] is inaugurated as the provisional President of the [[Confederate States of America]]. * 1861 &ndash; With [[Italian unification]] almost complete, [[Victor Emmanuel II of Italy|Victor Emmanuel II]] of [[Piedmont]], [[Savoy]] and [[Sardinia]] assumes the title of [[King of Italy]]. *[[1865]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: [[Union Army|Union]] forces under [[Major General]] [[William T. Sherman]] set the [[South Carolina State House]] on fire during the [[Columbia, South Carolina in the American Civil War|burning of Columbia]]. *[[1873]] &ndash; [[Bulgaria]]n revolutionary leader [[Vasil Levski]] is executed by [[hanging]] in [[Sofia]] by the [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] authorities. *[[1878]] &ndash; [[John Tunstall]] is murdered by [[outlaw]] [[Jesse Evans]], sparking the [[Lincoln County War]] in [[Lincoln County, New Mexico]]. *[[1885]] &ndash; ''[[Adventures of Huckleberry Finn]]'' by [[Mark Twain]] is published in the United States. *[[1900]] &ndash; [[Second Boer War]]: Imperial forces suffer their worst single-day loss of life on [[Bloody Sunday (1900)|Bloody Sunday]], the first day of the [[Battle of Paardeberg]]. *[[1906]] &ndash; [[Édouard de Laveleye]] forms the [[Belgian Olympic Committee]] in [[Brussels]]. *[[1911]] &ndash; The first official flight with [[airmail]] takes place from [[Allahabad]], [[United Provinces of Agra and Oudh|United Provinces]], [[British India]] (now India), when [[Henri Pequet]], a 23-year-old pilot, delivers 6,500 letters to [[Naini]], about {{Convert|10|km|mi}} away. *[[1930]] &ndash; While studying photographs taken in [[January]], [[Clyde Tombaugh]] discovers [[Pluto]]. * 1930 &ndash; [[Elm Farm Ollie]] becomes the first [[cattle|cow]] to fly in a [[fixed-wing aircraft]] and also the first cow to be milked in an aircraft. *[[1932]] &ndash; The [[Empire of Japan]] declares a puppet state of [[Manzhouguo]] (the obsolete Chinese name for [[Manchuria]]) independent from the [[Republic of China (1912–49)|Republic of China]] and installed former [[Emperor of China|Chinese Emperor]] [[Puyi|Aisin Gioro Puyi]] as Chief Executive of the State. *[[1938]] &ndash; [[Second Sino-Japanese War]]: During the [[Nanking Massacre]] the [[Nanjing|Nanking]] Safety Zone International Committee is renamed "Nanking International Rescue Committee" and the safety zone in place for refugees falls apart. *[[1942]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: The [[Imperial Japanese Army]] begins the [[Sook Ching|systematic extermination]] of perceived hostile elements among the [[Chinese in Singapore]]. *[[1943]] &ndash; World War II: The [[Nazism|Nazis]] arrest the members of the [[White Rose]] movement. * 1943 &ndash; World War II: [[Joseph Goebbels]] delivers his [[Sportpalast speech|''Sportpalast'' speech]]. *[[1946]] &ndash; Sailors of the [[Royal Indian Navy mutiny]] in [[Mumbai|Bombay]] harbour, from where the action spreads throughout the [[Presidencies and provinces of British India|Provinces of British India]], involving 78 ships, twenty shore establishments and 20,000 sailors *[[1947]] &ndash; [[First Indochina War]]: The French [[Battle of Hanoi|gain complete control]] of [[Hanoi]] after forcing the [[Viet Minh]] to withdraw to mountains. *[[1954]] &ndash; The first [[Church of Scientology]] is established in [[Los Angeles]]. *[[1955]] &ndash; [[Operation Teapot]]: Teapot test shot "Wasp" is successfully detonated at the [[Nevada Test Site]] with a yield of [[Effects of nuclear explosions#Summary of the effects|1.2 kilotons]]. Wasp is the first of fourteen shots in the Teapot series. *[[1957]] &ndash; [[Kenya]]n rebel leader [[Dedan Kimathi]] is executed by the British colonial government. * 1957 &ndash; [[Walter James Bolton]] becomes the last person [[Capital punishment in New Zealand|legally executed]] in New Zealand. *[[1965]] &ndash; [[The Gambia]] becomes independent from the United Kingdom. *[[1970]] &ndash; The [[Chicago Seven]] are found not guilty of conspiring to incite riots at the [[1968 Democratic National Convention]]. *[[1972]] &ndash; The [[California Supreme Court]] in the case of ''[[People v. Anderson]]'', (6 Cal.3d 628) invalidates the state's [[Capital punishment|death penalty]] and commutes the sentences of all [[death row]] inmates to life imprisonment. *[[1977]] &ndash; The [[Space Shuttle Enterprise|Space Shuttle ''Enterprise'']] test vehicle is carried on its maiden "flight" on top of a [[Boeing 747]]. *[[1979]] &ndash; [[Richard Petty]] wins a then-record sixth [[Daytona 500]] after leaders [[Donnie Allison]] and [[Cale Yarborough]] crash on the final lap of the first [[NASCAR]] race televised live flag-to-flag. *[[1983]] &ndash; Thirteen people die and one is seriously injured in the [[Wah Mee massacre]] in [[Seattle]]. It is said to be the largest robbery-motivated mass-murder in U.S. history. *[[1991]] &ndash; The [[Provisional Irish Republican Army|IRA]] [[Victoria station and Paddington station bombings|explodes bombs]] in the early morning at [[Paddington station]] and [[London Victoria station|Victoria station]] in London. *[[2001]] &ndash; [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] agent [[Robert Hanssen]] is arrested for spying for the [[Soviet Union]]. He is ultimately convicted and sentenced to life imprisonment. * 2001 &ndash; Seven-time [[NASCAR]] [[Sprint Cup Series]] champion [[Dale Earnhardt]] [[Death of Dale Earnhardt|dies in an accident]] during the [[Daytona 500]]. * 2001 &ndash; [[Sampit conflict]]: Inter-ethnic violence between [[Dayak people|Dayaks]] and [[Madura Island|Madurese]] breaks out in [[Sampit]], [[Central Kalimantan]], [[Indonesia]], ultimately resulting in more than 500 deaths and 100,000 Madurese displaced from their homes. *[[2003]] &ndash; Nearly 200 people die in the [[Daegu subway fire]] in South Korea. *[[2004]] &ndash; Up to 295 people, including nearly 200 rescue workers, die near [[Nishapur|Nishapur, Iran]] when a runaway freight train carrying [[sulfur]], [[petrol]] and [[fertilizer]] [[Nishapur train disaster|catches fire and explodes]]. *[[2007]] &ndash; [[2007 Samjhauta Express bombings|Samjhauta Express bombings]] occurred around midnight in [[Diwana railway station|Diwana]] near the Indian city of [[Panipat]], 80 kilometres (50 mi) north of [[New Delhi]], [[India]]. *[[2010]] &ndash; [[WikiLeaks]] publishes the first of hundreds of thousands of [[Classified information|classified documents]] disclosed by the soldier now known as [[Chelsea Manning]]. *[[2013]] &ndash; Armed robbers [[Brussels Airport diamond heist|steal]] a haul of diamonds worth $50 million during a raid at [[Brussels Airport]] in [[Belgium]]. *[[2014]] &ndash; At least 76 people are killed and hundreds are injured in [[February 2014 Euromaidan riots|clashes]] between riot police and demonstrators in [[Kiev|Kiev, Ukraine]].
