'''''Víkurfréttir''''' is the main [[newspaper]] of the [[Iceland]]ic town of [[Keflavík]].

The newspaper was founded in [[Southern Peninsula (Iceland)|Southern Peninsula]] in August 1980. In 1983, it was bought by the current owner, Páll Ketilsson. It is a weekly but was for a while published twice a week.<ref>[http://www.vf.is/um-bladid/ Um blaðið], Víkurfréttir {{is icon}}</ref>

